{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 2685, "title": "Make exception captures not delete shadowed vars", "body": "Fixes #2684.\r\n\r\nAs a side effect, this renames except-bound vars at compile time, but no one should be depending on the (compiled) name of exception vars. I hope.\r\n\r\nThis:\r\n```hy\r\n(setv e (try\r\n  (/ 1 0)\r\n  (except [e ZeroDivisionError]\r\n    e)))\r\n(print e)\r\n```\r\nnow compiles to this:\r\n```python\r\ntry:\r\n    e = 1 / 0\r\nexcept ZeroDivisionError as _hy_exc_e_2:\r\n    e = _hy_exc_e_2\r\nprint(e)\r\n```\r\nand successfully prints `division by zero`.", "baseRefName": "master", "baseRefOid": "ae2968552ee332ac551973fc381458371dfeaa6f", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "hylang/hy"}, "url": "https://github.com/hylang/hy/pull/2685", "createdAt": "2026-02-23T06:18:07Z", "mergedAt": "2026-02-26T13:14:04Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "hylang/hy"}, "sha": "ae2968552ee332ac551973fc381458371dfeaa6f"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/hylang/hy/pull/2685.diff", "number": 2685, "created_at": "2026-02-23T06:18:07Z", "merged_at": "2026-02-26T13:14:04Z", "resolved_issues": [2684]}
